Rating: 4
This was excellent! I've made this several times now and love it. We are big korean barbecue fans, and the marinade on this beef was so flavorful! We use a top sirloin steak instead, which came out tender (be careful not to overcook the steak- it's thin, it cooks fast). I also use brown jasmine rice instead of white, since I have it in the cupboard. I didn't bother looking for fleur de del, but used sea salt instead. I also find it's better to only use about half of the sesame salt mixture on the asparagus- the rest is delicious sprinkled on the rice! The kimchi is a key component to the bowl, adding spice and tanginess. I am very happy with this dish.

