Rating: 4
Delicious! The marinade for the meat was perfect, and the tip of freezing the steak allowed me to slice it extra thin, just as our favorite Korean BBQ place does. I did not make the sesame salt (no sesame seeds on hand). I just drizzled a little sesame oil on the asparagus and tossed with salt and chili powder. It was just fine. Don't skip the kim chee! It added great flavor to the dish. I would get a mild kim chee (not the hot) - we like spicy food, and the mild kim chee was plenty spicy.

Rating: 4
This was amazing!! Mouth watering, tasty, aromatic good! My family loved it so much that my 8 year old licked her bowl clean and then said, "Hey Mom, you forgot to give me dinner, can I have some?" She then put in a request for me to make it EVERY night! The only changes I made was to add some sugar snap peas with the asparagus (because my youngest doesn't like asparagus) and to use jasmine rice, because the only medium or short grain rice Whole Foods had was either $9 for one bag or short grain brown rice. The jasmine was fragrant and worked perfectly. It was especially good with the sesame salt sprinkled on top. My girls also think that now we should have rice & eggs for breakfast with the yummy sesame salt. This dish is going to definitely become part of our regular rotation.